    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i think i might be able to check it myself. what exactly am i looking for when i open it up? like are there certain parts that usually just stop working out of nowhere?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If you're going to venture in there, be careful, as these units have high-voltage components—don't touch anything until the power is completely off! You're looking for the main electrical components, especially the capacitor and the motor itself. A bad capacitor is a very common culprit for this kind of humming without spinning; it's like the battery that gives the motor the initial *oomph* to start up. If the capacitor is weak, the motor just hums, waiting for a charge that never quite comes.",
